item.title: Do you like Dubstep?
item.dc:creator: @jme jme
item.description:
@jme wrote:

[quote=“Cres, post:12, topic:517455”][quote author=Kidpaparoach link=topic=635713.msg4286837#msg4286837 date=1366478413]

2 mins is my limit for any dubstep song, Its hard to even get that far. repeats its self to often…

First time I see a ‘First Time Poster’ say somthing usefull and true.
Dubstep ain’t really amazing or anything… Any douche can download FLStudio, tweak at the buttons and mash up a beat.
I like Blackmill’s dubstep but like mikeyman said, the other songs get repetitive.

It’s your opinion it’s not a fact so don’t state it like it is. To you it may be repetitive but to others it may not be and so on. Music isn’t good nor (although it can have a bad/good creation can be LQ etc) bad, it is defined as good or bad by the listener. I hate when people slander genres they don’t like etc, that’s like me hating on mustard because I don’t like it (taste is in a similar situation as sound in this context).
[/quote]

If you hear the same part of the song 10 times before it’s finished, it’s repetitive (and that goes for everyone).
Yeah it totally depends on who listens it but hey…
That’s like saying “you’re not to say that killing people is bad, to some people it might be the best thing in the world so let everyone decide for themselves”.
And what you get then is a group of assholes sayin “leave us be, we like this shit, it’s our opinion”.
love no.
The shit they present you in chanels like UKF isn’t music (with some rare exceptions).
It’s dubstep, it’s sound, it’s noise, but it ain’t music.
And it angers me when people defend their shit because it already became such a big thing like loveing religion.
They KNOW it’s absolute shit but they keep loveing defending it and ‘contributing’ to it.
99% of the dubstep ‘songs’ brought there is like a goddamn terrorist bomb attack.[/quote]

I agree its repetitive, and hard to listen for long. I think that goes for electronic music in general, and especially club music. I don’t agree that it’s not music, it’s totally subjective. I think you just don’t like it and can’t comprehend how others do, the same way I feel about all metal.

But since it’s repetitive, thats why I’d rather listen to a mix. Everyone has probably heard these already, and it’s not really dubstep (maybe at times it is)
[youtube]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JJXf-rn-iKc[/youtube]
[youtube]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FDGuMFt2MF0[/youtube]
